Date: Fri 31 Aug 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information [edited]
<www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=27718>


Equine influenza, Colombia
-------------------
Information received on 31 Aug 2018 from Dr Luis Humberto Martinez Lacouture, Gerente General, Instituto Colombiano Agropecuario (ICA), Ministerio de Agricultura y Desarrollo Rural, Bogota, Colombia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 18 Jun 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Jul 2018
Report date: 31 Aug 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 31 Aug 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 3 May 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: equine influenza virus
Serotype: H3N8
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (245)
[The 245 outbreaks of equine influenza occurred in the following departments: Valle del Cauca (47), Antioquia (31), Risaralda (16), Caldas (11), Boyaca (6), Cundinamarca (17), Bolivar (15), Tolima (13), Quindio (44), Cauca (12), Santander (18), Norte de Santander (3), Huila (6), Narino (2), Cordoba (2), Putumayo (2). See details of each outbreak at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 245
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 6376 / 2763 / 1 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae/ 43.33 / 0.02 / 0.04 / 0.02
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, quarantine, disinfection, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (national laboratory) / Equidae / agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID) / 28 Jul 2018 / positive
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (national laboratory)/ Equidae / haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT) / 28 Jul 2018 / positive
National Veterinary Diagnosis Laboratory (National laboratory)/ Equidae / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 28 Jul 2018 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[To date (Tue 4 Sep 2018), 16 of 32 departments are affected with equine influenza. Based on information provided to the OIE, Colombia has about 1.5 million horses (<www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Countryinformation/Animalpopulation>).

You can find information bulletins and recommendations that Instituto Colombiano Agropecuario (ICA) has published on the current equine influenza event in Colombia (this information is available in Spanish) at the following link: https://www.ica.gov.co/ICAComunica/PYP/influenzaequina.aspx. - Mod.CRD

